# Cap - Godot & GDScript Presentation

## Architecture
- `src/Godot/`: **GDScript** (`.gd`/`.tscn`) for presentation — input, scenes, 3D transforms, meshes, and UI.
- Presentation-only in `.gd`; simulation logic stays in Core or CoreBridge `RefCounted` handles.

## Godot & GDScript Rules
- Godot 4; static types on GDScript vars, params, and returns.
- Scene wiring: `@export`, `@onready`; use `@tool` only when editor behavior is needed.
- Signals: `.connect(callable)` — avoid string-based signal names.
- **3D rendering discipline**: reuse/pool visualizer nodes; avoid spawning a new node per item/tick; batch mesh updates where possible.
- Style: snake_case functions/variables; PascalCase `class_name`.
